events.name: Boston Celtics at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — RJ Barrett banked in a 3-pointer at the buzzer to give the New York Knicks 108-105 comeback victory over the Boston Celtics on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: RJ Barrett banks in 3 at buzzer, Knicks beat Celtics 108-105

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had 22 points, nine rebounds and six assists and Memphis built an early lead and coasted to a 118-88 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Thursday night, the Grizzlies’ seventh straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant, Grizzlies rout lowly Pistons for 7th straight win

events.name: Golden State Warriors at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram broke out of a shooting slump with 32 points and the New Orleans Pelicans snapped a three-game skid with a 101-96 victory over the depleted Golden State Warriors on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram scores 32, Pelicans beat depleted Warriors 101-96

headlines.description: — Chris Paul and the Phoenix Suns have turned into some of the league's best closers. It's a big reason they've reached 30 wins before any other team in the NBA this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul has triple-double, NBA-leading Suns top Clippers 106-89
